---
source: crates/cli/tests/integration/cli_help_test.rs
description: |
  Parity snapshot of `newton --help` after spec 051 moves `run` under `workflow`.
  `run` is now a hidden deprecated alias; its summary is updated accordingly.
  Lines under "Commands:" are sorted alphabetically; cli-framework returns
  them in HashMap order, which is non-deterministic across runs.
---
Usage: newton <COMMAND>

Commands:
  batch       Process queued work items for a project
  completion  Emit shell completion script
  config      Inspect resolved Newton configuration
  data        Catalog CRUD via HTTP-style verbs (get/post/put/patch/delete)
  doctor      Run local environment diagnostic probes
  health      Print a one-line liveness status
  help        Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
  init        Initialize a Newton workspace with the default template
  mcp         MCP server management
  run         Execute a workflow graph (deprecated — use `newton workflow run`)
  serve       Start the Newton HTTP API server
  spec        Export the CLI command surface as JSON, YAML, or Markdown
  version     Print version information
  webhook     Run webhooks to trigger workflows from external events
  workflow    Operate on workflow YAML files or manage execution lifecycle (validate/lint/preview/graph/run/resume/runs/checkpoint/artifact)

Options:
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version
